<div id="content_table" style="width: 866px;"   >
<br><br>
<h1 class="h1_blue_dark">Writer's Block</h1>



  
<table width="866px" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" cellpadding="5" border=0>
<tr><td>
<div>
<h1 class="h1_gray">Introduction</h1>
<br>
Do you sometimes struggle when you write a paper?   Do you ever have trouble coming up with ideas? 
 Do you get stuck halfway through and want to give up?  If you answered “yes” to any of these questions, 
 then you’re in a class with the greatest writers of all time!  Writing is hard work, and no matter how good a 
 writer you are, you will often struggle with “writer’s block”—that feeling of hitting a wall during the writing process.  
 This workshop will give you some strategies for dealing with writer’s block.  Since most of your college courses 
 require written work such as essays and term papers, you’ll have many opportunities to apply the strategies throughout 
 your academic career—and beyond.<br><br>
</div>
</td></tr>


<tr><td><table width="866px" class="border_green" border=0>
	<tr>
	<td><div>

<strong>By the end of this activity, you should be able to:</strong> <br><br>

	<ul class="c">
		<li>Define or describe “writer’s block” </li>
		<li>Identify common causes of writer’s block </li>
		<li>Apply strategies for overcoming writer’s block </li>
	</ul>
</div>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table></td></tr>

<tr><td><div>
<br><br>
<h1 class="h1_gray">Let's get started!</h1><br>

<strong>If at any time you need help, please ask a tutor.</strong><br><br>
</div></td></tr>
<!-- this is the steps table -->
<tr><td>
<table width="866px" border=0>
<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 1: </h1></td>
<td valign="bottom"><div>First you'll need to make sure you have the handouts for this activity. 
If you don't, ask a tutor to help you.<br><br></div></td></tr>

<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 2: </h1></td>
<td><div>To start thinking about how writer's block affects you, please find the handout called "Writer’s Block − Warm-up Activity" 
and fill-in the table in it.
<br><br></div></td></tr>

<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 3: </h1></td>
<td><div>Watch this 
<a href="Powerpoint Writer's Block.ppt">PowerPoint</a> presentation on how to overcome writer's block.
<br><br></div></td></tr>

<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 4: </h1></td>
<td><div>Find the handout called "Writer’s Block – Worksheet" and complete all the parts in it (A,B,C and D).  
Note that in the workshop exercises, the activities are completed as a group, but in this 
guided learning activity, you will work on your own. The tutor will review your responses with you at the end. 
<br><br>
STOP and review your worksheet with a tutor.
<br><br></div></td></tr>



<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 5: </h1></td>
<td><div>Complete the self-reflection in the handouts.<br><br>
</div></td></tr>

<tr><td width="80px" valign="top"><h1 class="h1_gray">Step 6: </h1></td>
<td><div>Review your work with a tutor.<br><br>
</div></td></tr>

</table>
</td></tr>
         
<tr><td><div>

<h1 class="h1_gray">That's it. You are done! Thank you for completing this guided learning activity.</h1>
</div></td></tr>                  
                  



